44:08.406 --> 44:09.628
At least she did at that time.

44:10.088 --> 44:14.674
And she phoned him and asked where, she phoned Andreas,

44:14.992 --> 44:18.836
and asked where she could find evidence of what had been published in Russia.

44:19.616 --> 44:22.339
And he told her, it's all there in Hanneman's Hemingway.

44:22.819 --> 44:26.463
And he said, after a dead silence, she says, it's right here on my desk.

44:28.084 --> 44:29.225
That's a great story.

44:29.286 --> 44:33.109
And she's the one that didn't want you to make any money on it, right?

44:33.630 --> 44:34.751
Well, no, no.

44:34.991 --> 44:35.772
She was afraid.

44:36.192 --> 44:37.253
She was afraid I was in.

44:37.593 --> 44:38.334
No, no, no.

44:38.394 --> 44:39.075
I didn't mean to see.

44:39.115 --> 44:40.596
I obviously misspoke.

44:41.257 --> 44:42.518
Well, she was concerned.

44:42.852 --> 44:52.325
was that I was going to be in for a big shock, that this wasn't going to earn me a whole lot of money, you know, becauseâ Oh, I see.

44:52.345 --> 44:52.625
I'm sorry.

44:52.645 --> 44:53.386
I misunderstood.

44:53.626 --> 44:53.907
Yes.

44:54.287 --> 44:55.389
